---
// Workspace chat page. Reads ?id=<chatId> from the URL since Astro
// static-mode can't dynamic-route to user-generated UUIDs at runtime.
// All data + streaming happens client-side.
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8" />
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
<title>Chat — Legal Overflow</title>
<meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
<link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
<link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=Geist:wght@300;400;500;600&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/site-anim.css" />
<script src="/nav-autohide.js" defer></script>
<script src="/site-dialog.js" defer></script>
<script src="/site-anim.js" defer></script>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/workspace.css" />
<style is:global>
  /* ============================================================
     Chat page — page-local stylesheet
     is:global because messages are rendered via JS and would lose
     Astro auto-scoped attributes. Page-localness is enforced by the
     body.ws-chat ancestor selector — rules cannot leak.
     Verbatim port of the design prototype, mapped onto the existing
     class names so all JS handlers continue to work.
     ============================================================ */

  body.ws-chat {
    --rule-thread: #cbc4b1;
    --tick: #a39b85;
    --motion-snap: cubic-bezier(.2,.8,.2,1);
    --privacy: #c98a14;
    --privacy-tint: #f4ead0;
    /* Teal (blueish-green) signals an ACTIVE workflow / prompt-pack
       chat. Same usage pattern as --privacy: tints the chat
       container, accents the border, drives the pulsing top stripe.
       Distinct hue so privacy and workflow can coexist visually
       (they apply to different areas) and never look like the
       same state. */
    --workflow: #2a8a89;
    --workflow-tint: #d8eded;
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(1200px 600px at 80% -10%, rgba(208,219,213,.18), transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(900px 500px at -10% 30%, rgba(220,212,196,.25), transparent 70%);
  }

  /* ---------- shell layout ----------
     IMPORTANT: must keep the 3-column grid (rail / 6px handle /
     chat-main) that workspace.css set up, otherwise the chat-main
     gets pushed off the grid. Just adjust the rail width. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-shell {
    --rail-width: 280px;
    position: relative; z-index: 2;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: var(--rail-width) 6px 1fr;
    border-top: none;       /* defeat workspace.css */
    max-width: 1400px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: transparent;
  }
  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    body.ws-chat .chat-shell { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    body.ws-chat .chat-rail   { display: none; }
    body.ws-chat #rail-resize { display: none; }
  }

  /* ---------- sidebar (chat-rail) ---------- */
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail {
    position: relative;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px;
    padding: 14px 14px 4px 6px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    min-height: 0;
    min-width: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: transparent;
    transition: opacity .18s var(--motion-snap);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail .side-list {
    overflow-y: auto;
    overflow-x: hidden;
    padding-right: 4px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 6px; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 3px; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-back {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    color: var(--ink-3); letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 4px 4px 0;
    text-decoration: none;
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    background: transparent !important;     /* defeat workspace.css hover bg */
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-back:hover { color: var(--ink); }

  /* sidebar head — kicker + title + pulse pip */
  body.ws-chat .side-head {
    display: flex !important; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px;
    padding: 4px 4px 0;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat #new-chat,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail .chat-rail-new {
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .side-search { flex-shrink: 0; }
  body.ws-chat .side-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-3);
    letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase;
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .side-kicker .pip {
    width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent-deep);
    animation: chatPulseDim 2s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  @keyframes chatPulseDim { 0%,100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: .35; } }
  body.ws-chat .side-title {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 22px;
    letter-spacing: -.005em; color: var(--ink);
    line-height: 1.1;
  }
  body.ws-chat .side-title em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent-deep); }

  /* sidebar search */
  body.ws-chat .side-search {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 4px;
    padding: 8px 10px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4);
    transition: border-color .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .side-search:focus-within { border-color: var(--ink); }
  body.ws-chat .side-search svg { width: 12px; height: 12px; color: var(--ink-3); flex-shrink: 0; }
  body.ws-chat .side-search input {
    border: none; outline: none; background: transparent;
    font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 13px; color: var(--ink);
    width: 100%;
  }
  body.ws-chat .side-search input::placeholder { color: var(--ink-4); }
  body.ws-chat .side-search .kbd {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-3);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-thread); border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 1px 5px;
  }

  /* section labels in sidebar (added by JS that groups items) */
  body.ws-chat .side-section-l {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-4);
    letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 14px 4px 4px;
    display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: baseline;
  }
  body.ws-chat .side-section-l span:last-child { color: var(--ink-4); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-new,
  body.ws-chat #new-chat {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between; gap: 10px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 11px 14px; cursor: pointer;
    background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background .15s var(--motion-snap), border-color .15s, transform .12s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-new:hover,
  body.ws-chat #new-chat:hover { background: var(--accent-deep); border-color: var(--accent-deep); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-new:active,
  body.ws-chat #new-chat:active { transform: translateY(1px); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list {
    flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; min-height: 0;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0;
    padding-right: 4px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 6px; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 3px; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list a,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-item,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 3px;
    padding: 8px 12px 8px 10px;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--rule-soft);
    cursor: pointer; text-decoration: none;
    position: relative;
    color: var(--ink);
    min-width: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: background .15s var(--motion-snap), padding-left .15s var(--motion-snap);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list a:hover,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-item:hover,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item:hover {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4); padding-left: 14px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list a.is-active,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-item.is-active,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item.is-active {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.55); padding-left: 14px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list a.is-active::before,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-item.is-active::before,
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item.is-active::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; top: 8px; bottom: 8px;
    width: 2px; background: var(--accent-deep);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item-title {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--ink);
    white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;
    max-width: 100%;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item-meta {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-3);
    letter-spacing: .04em;
    white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis;
    max-width: 100%;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item-meta .dot {
    width: 2px; height: 2px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--ink-4);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    /* Hide the "·" character — we render the dot via CSS for consistent sizing */
    color: transparent; font-size: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .side-item-meta .priv {
    color: var(--privacy); letter-spacing: .12em; font-weight: 500;
  }
  /* Delete button — only show on row hover */
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .rail-row-del {
    position: absolute !important; top: 6px; right: 6px;
    width: 18px; height: 18px; padding: 0;
    background: transparent; border: 1px solid transparent;
    color: var(--ink-4); font-size: 12px; line-height: 1;
    border-radius: 3px; cursor: pointer;
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity .15s, background .15s, color .15s, border-color .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .rail-row-wrap:hover .rail-row-del { opacity: 1; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .rail-row-del:hover {
    background: #b22222; color: white; border-color: #b22222;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-rail-list .rail-row-wrap {
    position: relative;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  body.ws-chat #rail-resize {
    width: 7px; cursor: ew-resize; z-index: 5;
    background: transparent;
    align-self: stretch;
    position: relative;
    transition: background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat #rail-resize::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%,-50%);
    width: 1px; height: 32px; background: var(--rule-soft);
    transition: background .15s, height .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat #rail-resize:hover::before,
  body.ws-chat #rail-resize.is-dragging::before {
    background: var(--ink); height: 56px;
  }

  /* ---------- main chat column ---------- */
  body.ws-chat .chat-main {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    min-height: 0;
    padding-left: 24px;
    position: relative;
    background: transparent;
  }

  /* ---------- chat-head with corner brackets — compact ----------
     Tight padding + smaller title so the chat container gets max room.
     Forced display: block to defeat workspace.css's flex layout. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-head {
    position: relative !important;
    display: flex !important;
    flex-direction: column !important;
    padding: 10px 16px 12px !important;
    margin: 0 0 0 !important;
    background: transparent !important;
    border-bottom: none !important;
    flex: none !important;
    align-items: initial !important;
    gap: 0 !important;
    transition: padding .12s ease;
  }
  /* Reorder so the action row (model picker + buttons) sits FIRST
     in flex order. When the user shrinks the header, the LOWER
     rows (kicker / meta / anchors) collapse first while the
     button row stays anchored at the top — always clickable. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-head-row { order: 1; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-kicker   { order: 2; margin: 6px 0 0 !important; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-meta     { order: 3; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-anchors  { order: 4; }
  /* Compact mode — applied by the resize JS once the user drags
     the handle past the "make-it-tighter" threshold. Hides all
     ancillary rows but PRESERVES the action button row. The chat
     stream area below grows accordingly. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-head[data-compact="1"] {
    padding: 6px 16px 6px !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head[data-compact="1"] .chat-kicker,
  body.ws-chat .chat-head[data-compact="1"] .chat-meta,
  body.ws-chat .chat-head[data-compact="1"] .chat-anchors {
    display: none !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head[data-compact="1"] .chat-title-input {
    font-size: 15px !important;
    line-height: 1.2 !important;
  }
  /* Hides ONLY the meta strip when the user wants a slightly more
     compact header but still wants the anchor chips visible. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-head[data-compact="meta"] .chat-meta {
    display: none !important;
  }
  /* Horizontal resize handle pinned to the bottom edge of the
     header. Same visual language as the sidebar's vertical
     #rail-resize handle: a thin centered nub that grows on hover/
     drag. Drag vertically to grow/shrink the header. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-head-resize {
    position: relative;
    height: 7px;
    margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    cursor: ns-resize;
    background: transparent;
    z-index: 5;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head-resize::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 50%; top: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    width: 32px; height: 1px; background: var(--rule-soft);
    transition: background .15s, width .15s, height .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head-resize:hover::before,
  body.ws-chat .chat-head-resize.is-dragging::before {
    background: var(--ink); width: 56px; height: 2px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head::before, body.ws-chat .chat-head::after,
  body.ws-chat .chat-head > .br-bl, body.ws-chat .chat-head > .br-br {
    width: 9px; height: 9px;     /* smaller corners */
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-kicker,
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-head-row,
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-meta {
    display: flex !important;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-kicker {
    display: inline-flex !important;
    margin-bottom: 6px !important;       /* tighter than the prototype */
    font-size: 9.5px !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-meta {
    margin-top: 6px !important;
    font-size: 9.5px !important;
    gap: 14px !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head::before, body.ws-chat .chat-head::after,
  body.ws-chat .chat-head > .br-bl, body.ws-chat .chat-head > .br-br {
    content: ''; position: absolute; width: 14px; height: 14px;
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); pointer-events: none;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head::before { top: 0; left: 0; border-right: none; border-bottom: none; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head::after  { top: 0; right: 0; border-left: none; border-bottom: none; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head > .br-bl { bottom: 0; left: 0; border-top: none; border-right: none; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head > .br-br { bottom: 0; right: 0; border-top: none; border-left: none; }

  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-kicker {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 12px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10.5px; color: var(--accent-deep);
    letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-kicker .k-tag {
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-deep); padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 2px;
    font-size: 9.5px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-head .chat-kicker .k-coord { color: var(--ink-4); font-size: 9.5px; }

  body.ws-chat .chat-head-row {
    display: flex; gap: 14px; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-title-input {
    flex: 1; min-width: 200px;
    font-family: var(--serif); font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(18px, 1.8vw, 22px);   /* much smaller — was clamp(28px,3.4vw,44px) */
    letter-spacing: -.005em; line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0; padding: 2px 0;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: transparent; border: none; outline: none;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-title-input::placeholder { color: var(--ink-4); font-style: italic; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-title-input:focus { box-shadow: inset 0 -1px 0 var(--accent-deep); }

  body.ws-chat .chat-head-right {
    display: flex; gap: 8px; align-items: center; flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  /* project pill — keep existing functionality, restyle */
  body.ws-chat .chat-project-pill {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 6px 11px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-project-pill:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-project-pill.has-project { color: var(--accent-deep); border-color: var(--accent-deep); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-project-pill-caret { font-size: 8px; opacity: .6; }

  body.ws-chat .chat-save-convo-btn {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 6px 11px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-save-convo-btn:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-save-convo-btn:disabled { opacity: .45; cursor: not-allowed; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-save-convo-btn svg { width: 11px; height: 11px; flex-shrink: 0; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-save-convo-btn.is-saved {
    color: var(--accent-deep); border-color: var(--accent-deep); background: rgba(10,125,87,.06);
  }

  /* model select — restyle as bordered mono pill */
  body.ws-chat .chat-model-select,
  body.ws-chat #model-select {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 7px 11px;
    color: var(--ink); background: rgba(255,255,255,.4);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat #model-select:hover {
    color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); background: rgba(255,255,255,.65);
  }

  /* privacy toggle (existing structure: label > checkbox + label-text) */
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    padding: 6px 11px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle input[type="checkbox"] {
    appearance: none; -webkit-appearance: none;
    width: 22px; height: 12px; border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--rule-soft);
    position: relative; margin: 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background .15s var(--motion-snap);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle input[type="checkbox"]::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 1px; top: 1px;
    width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--ink-4);
    transition: transform .2s var(--motion-snap), border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle input[type="checkbox"]:checked {
    background: var(--privacy);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle input[type="checkbox"]:checked::after {
    transform: translateX(10px); border-color: var(--privacy); background: var(--privacy-tint);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle:has(input:checked) {
    color: var(--privacy); border-color: var(--privacy); background: var(--privacy-tint);
  }

  /* Deep-think toggle — same pill shape as the privacy toggle, but
     accent-colored when on (signals reasoning-mode rather than
     privacy-mode). Hidden via the [hidden] attribute when the
     selected model doesn't support reasoning. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-deep-think-toggle {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
    padding: 6px 11px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 4px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-deep-think-toggle:hover { color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-deep-think-toggle input[type="checkbox"] {
    appearance: none; -webkit-appearance: none;
    width: 22px; height: 12px; border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--rule-soft);
    position: relative; margin: 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background .15s var(--motion-snap);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-deep-think-toggle input[type="checkbox"]::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 1px; top: 1px;
    width: 10px; height: 10px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--paper); border: 1px solid var(--ink-4);
    transition: transform .2s var(--motion-snap), border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-deep-think-toggle input[type="checkbox"]:checked {
    background: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-deep-think-toggle input[type="checkbox"]:checked::after {
    transform: translateX(10px); border-color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa); background: rgba(56, 98, 170, .15);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-deep-think-toggle:has(input:checked) {
    color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa); border-color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa); background: rgba(56, 98, 170, .08);
  }

  /* Anchor chip strip — pinned vault docs + post-turn suggestions.
     Sits in the chat header right under the meta line. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-anchors {
    display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px; align-items: center;
    margin-top: 10px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-anchors .chat-anchors-label {
    color: var(--ink-4); margin-right: 4px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-anchor-chip {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 4px 8px;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: rgba(56, 98, 170, .06);
    color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-anchor-chip .chat-anchor-x {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    width: 14px; height: 14px; padding: 0;
    border: none; background: transparent;
    color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa); cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 13px; line-height: 1;
    opacity: .65;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-anchor-chip .chat-anchor-x:hover { opacity: 1; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-anchor-suggest {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 4px 8px;
    border: 1px dashed var(--rule-soft);
    border-radius: 3px;
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-anchor-suggest:hover {
    color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
    border-color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
    background: rgba(56, 98, 170, .04);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-privacy-toggle-lock { display: none; }     /* design uses pill instead of lock emoji */

  /* Workflow chip — shown in the anchor strip when the chat is
     bound to a saved prompt pack. Teal to match the active-mode
     tint applied to the chat container so the "you're in a
     workflow" signal is visually consistent. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-chip {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 4px 9px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--workflow);
    background: var(--workflow-tint);
    border: 1px solid var(--workflow);
    border-radius: 3px;
    cursor: help;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-chip-icon {
    font-size: 12px; line-height: 1;
  }

  /* Intro card shown in the empty messages area when a workflow
     is loaded but no messages yet. Teal to match the chip and
     the chat-container tint. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-intro {
    margin: 32px auto;
    padding: 20px 22px;
    max-width: 540px;
    background: rgba(42, 138, 137, .05);
    border: 1px solid var(--workflow);
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-family: var(--sans);
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-intro-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--workflow);
    margin-bottom: 6px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-intro-title {
    font-family: var(--serif, Georgia, serif);
    font-size: 22px; font-weight: 400;
    margin: 0 0 8px 0;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-intro-desc {
    font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    margin: 0 0 12px 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-intro-meta {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: .04em;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-workflow-intro-cta {
    font-size: 13px; line-height: 1.45;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    padding-top: 10px;
    border-top: 1px dashed var(--rule-soft);
  }

  body.ws-chat .chat-key-source {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px; color: var(--accent-deep);
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    align-self: center;
  }

  /* Vision-capability hint — appears next to the model picker when
     the selected model can read images attached from the vault.
     Same monospace caption style as the key-source pill so the
     header reads as a coherent metadata strip. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-vision-hint {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ins, #4a8a64);
    align-self: center;
    padding: 2px 7px;
    border: 1px solid currentColor;
    border-radius: 2px;
    cursor: help;
  }

  /* meta line below the title — stats row */
  body.ws-chat .chat-meta {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--ink-3);
    letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-top: 12px;
    display: flex; gap: 18px; flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-meta b { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-meta .ml { color: var(--ink-4); }

  /* privacy banner — shows when privacy mode is on */
  body.ws-chat .privacy-banner {
    display: none;
    padding: 8px 18px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; color: var(--privacy);
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--privacy);
    background: rgba(243,234,208,.5);
    align-items: center; gap: 10px;
    position: relative; z-index: 1;
  }
  body.ws-chat.privacy .privacy-banner,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on .privacy-banner { display: flex; }
  body.ws-chat .privacy-banner .pb-pip {
    width: 6px; height: 6px; border-radius: 50%; background: var(--privacy);
    animation: chatPulseDim 1.6s ease-in-out infinite;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .privacy-banner b { font-weight: 500; color: var(--ink); }

  /* suggested prompts — empty state */
  body.ws-chat .chat-empty {
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 28px;
    padding: 42px 20px;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
    color: inherit;
    font-style: normal;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-empty-text {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 18px; font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  body.ws-chat .suggested {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr); gap: 10px;
    max-width: 1080px; margin: 0 auto; width: 100%;
  }
  @media (max-width: 1100px) { body.ws-chat .suggested { grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr); } }
  @media (max-width:  680px) { body.ws-chat .suggested { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  body.ws-chat .suggested-head {
    grid-column: 1 / -1;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; letter-spacing: .14em;
    color: var(--ink-4); text-transform: uppercase;
    text-align: center;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .sg-card {
    text-align: left;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 6px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.35);
    padding: 12px 14px;
    cursor: pointer;
    position: relative;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px;
    transition: border-color .15s, transform .15s var(--motion-snap), background .15s;
    color: inherit;
    font: inherit;
  }
  body.ws-chat .sg-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--ink); background: rgba(255,255,255,.55); transform: translateY(-1px);
  }
  body.ws-chat .sg-card::before, body.ws-chat .sg-card::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; width: 8px; height: 8px;
    border-color: var(--ink-4); pointer-events: none;
    transition: border-color .15s, width .15s var(--motion-snap), height .15s var(--motion-snap);
  }
  body.ws-chat .sg-card::before { top: 4px; left: 4px; border-top: 1px solid; border-left: 1px solid; }
  body.ws-chat .sg-card::after  { bottom: 4px; right: 4px; border-bottom: 1px solid; border-right: 1px solid; }
  body.ws-chat .sg-card:hover::before, body.ws-chat .sg-card:hover::after {
    border-color: var(--accent-deep); width: 12px; height: 12px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .sg-cat {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px; letter-spacing: .14em;
    color: var(--ink-4); text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  body.ws-chat .sg-prompt {
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 14.5px; line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--ink);
  }
  body.ws-chat .sg-prompt em { font-style: italic; color: var(--accent-deep); }

  /* msg-meta line — mono uppercase per prototype */
  body.ws-chat .msg-meta {
    display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-4);
    letter-spacing: .14em; text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 4px 0 0;
  }

  /* citation/verify pill (existing JS produces .msg-verify-pill, .msg-link, .msg-link-pending) */
  body.ws-chat .msg-link {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--accent-deep);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-deep); border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 0 5px; margin: 0 1px;
    letter-spacing: .04em;
    text-decoration: none;
    background: transparent;
    transition: background .15s, color .15s;
    font-style: normal;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-link:hover { background: var(--accent-deep); color: var(--paper); }
  body.ws-chat .msg-link-pending {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px; font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--privacy);
    border: 1px solid var(--privacy); border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 0 5px; margin: 0 1px;
    letter-spacing: .04em;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-footref {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9px;
    color: var(--accent-deep);
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-verify-pill {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 4px 10px; margin-top: 8px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 3px;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    cursor: default;
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-verify-pill.is-complete {
    color: var(--accent-deep); border-color: var(--accent-deep);
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-verify-clickable { cursor: pointer; }
  body.ws-chat .msg-verify-clickable:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,.65); }
  body.ws-chat .msg-verify-caret { font-size: 8px; opacity: .7; }

  /* msg-actions row — Save / Copy / Refine matched to prototype */
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions {
    display: flex; gap: 0;
    margin-top: 6px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions button,
  body.ws-chat .msg-action,
  body.ws-chat .msg-copy {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-3);
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    background: transparent; border: none; cursor: pointer;
    padding: 5px 9px;
    border-right: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    transition: color .15s;
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions button:last-child,
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions .msg-copy:last-child { border-right: none; }
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions button:first-child,
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions .msg-copy:first-child { padding-left: 0; }
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions button:hover,
  body.ws-chat .msg-action:hover,
  body.ws-chat .msg-copy:hover { color: var(--accent-deep); }
  body.ws-chat .msg-actions svg { width: 11px; height: 11px; }

  /* msg-attach (paperclip chip inside user message) */
  body.ws-chat .msg-attach {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: .04em; color: var(--ink-2);
    background: rgba(0,0,0,.04); border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    border-radius: 999px; padding: 2px 8px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-attach-row { display: flex; gap: 5px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 8px; }

  /* status / cursor while streaming */
  body.ws-chat .msg-status {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--accent-deep);
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-status-spinner {
    width: 8px; height: 8px; border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent-deep);
    animation: chatPulseDim 1.2s ease-in-out infinite;
  }
  body.ws-chat .cursor {
    display: inline-block; width: 6px; height: 14px;
    background: var(--ink); margin-left: 2px;
    vertical-align: -2px;
    animation: chatBlink 1s steps(2,end) infinite;
  }
  @keyframes chatBlink { 50% { opacity: 0; } }
  body.ws-chat .msg-error {
    display: inline-block;
    color: #722;
    background: rgba(178,34,34,.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(178,34,34,.25);
    border-radius: 6px; padding: 8px 12px;
    font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic;
    font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.5;
  }

  /* sec-div above the chat container — tight to the container */
  body.ws-chat .chat-main .sec-div {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
    align-items: center; gap: 16px;
    margin: 0 0 8px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-3);
    letter-spacing: .12em; text-transform: uppercase;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-main .sec-div .sec-num { color: var(--ink); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-main .sec-div .sec-rule { height: 1px; background: var(--rule-soft); }
  body.ws-chat .chat-main .sec-div .sec-meta { color: var(--ink-4); font-size: 9.5px; }

  /* ---------- chat container (wraps messages + composer) ---------- */
  body.ws-chat .chat-container {
    position: relative;
    flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    border-radius: 8px;
    background: var(--paper-2);
    overflow: hidden;
    min-height: 0;        /* let it shrink under flex; flex:1 fills remaining space */
    transition: border-color .25s var(--motion-snap), background .25s;
  }
  body.ws-chat.privacy .chat-container,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on .chat-container {
    background: var(--privacy-tint);
    border-color: var(--privacy);
  }
  body.ws-chat.privacy .chat-container::before,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on .chat-container::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; right: 0; top: 0; height: 2px;
    background: var(--privacy);
    animation: chatPrivacyPulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  @keyframes chatPrivacyPulse { 0%,100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: .4; } }

  /* ---- Workflow / prompt-pack active state ----
     When the chat is running a prompt-pack workflow imported from
     the homepage, the chat container picks up the teal --workflow
     tint + accented border + a pulsing top stripe. Same visual
     language as privacy mode but different hue so the two can
     coexist (a chat can be both privacy-on AND running a workflow). */
  body.ws-chat.workflow-active .chat-container,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-workflow-on .chat-container {
    background: var(--workflow-tint);
    border-color: var(--workflow);
  }
  body.ws-chat.workflow-active .chat-container::before,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-workflow-on .chat-container::before {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; right: 0; top: 0; height: 2px;
    background: var(--workflow);
    animation: chatWorkflowPulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
    z-index: 1;
  }
  @keyframes chatWorkflowPulse { 0%,100% { opacity: 1; } 50% { opacity: .45; } }
  /* When BOTH privacy and workflow are on, the workflow stripe sits
     directly under the privacy stripe (offset 2px). Stack them so
     both states are visible. */
  body.ws-chat.privacy.workflow-active .chat-container::after {
    content: ''; position: absolute; left: 0; right: 0; top: 2px; height: 2px;
    background: var(--workflow);
    animation: chatWorkflowPulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  /* messages stream */
  body.ws-chat .chat-messages {
    flex: 1; overflow-y: auto; min-height: 0;
    padding: 24px 28px 18px;
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 22px;
    background: transparent;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-messages::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 8px; }
  body.ws-chat .chat-messages::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 4px; }

  /* empty state */
  body.ws-chat .chat-empty {
    text-align: center; color: var(--ink-3);
    font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 18px; font-style: italic;
    margin: 60px auto 0;
    max-width: 56ch;
  }

  /* user / assistant messages — system-UI sans like ChatGPT/Claude.
     Decoupled from the site's serif so the chat reads as a proper
     conversational interface. The composer above uses the same font
     for one-to-one parity between what you type and what you read. */
  body.ws-chat {
    --chat-font: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, "Segoe UI",
                 "Helvetica Neue", Arial, "Inter", "Liberation Sans",
                 sans-serif;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.user {
    align-self: flex-start; max-width: 78ch; width: 100%;
    background: transparent; border: none; padding: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.user .msg-body {
    font-family: var(--chat-font);
    font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.55;
    color: var(--ink);
    padding: 12px 16px;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.5);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    border-left: 2px solid var(--ink);
    border-radius: 0 4px 4px 0;
    letter-spacing: -.005em;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant {
    align-self: flex-start; max-width: 78ch; width: 100%;
    padding: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body {
    font-family: var(--chat-font) !important;
    font-size: 15px !important;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -.005em;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body p,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body p { margin: 0 0 12px; }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body p:last-child,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body strong,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body strong { font-weight: 600; }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body code,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body code {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 13px;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,.05);
    padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 3px;
  }
  /* assistant message headings (msg-h1 / h2 / h3) — keep them sans,
     just bigger / heavier for visual hierarchy */
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body .msg-h1,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body .msg-h1 {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--chat-font); font-weight: 600; font-size: 19px;
    line-height: 1.25; margin: 14px 0 6px; color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -.01em;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body .msg-h2,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body .msg-h2 {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--chat-font); font-weight: 600; font-size: 16.5px;
    line-height: 1.3; margin: 12px 0 4px; color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -.005em;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body .msg-h3,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body .msg-h3 {
    display: block;
    font-family: var(--chat-font); font-weight: 600; font-size: 14.5px;
    margin: 10px 0 4px; color: var(--ink);
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body ul,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body ul,
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body ol,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body ol {
    margin: 6px 0 12px; padding-left: 22px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg.asst .msg-body li,
  body.ws-chat .msg.assistant .msg-body li { margin: 2px 0; }

  /* ---------- composer area inside the container ---------- */
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    padding: 10px 18px 14px;
    background: var(--paper);
    display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 10px;
  }
  body.ws-chat.privacy .chat-composer,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on .chat-composer {
    background: var(--privacy-tint); border-top-color: var(--privacy);
  }
  /* Drag-target visual — composer grows a dashed accent border + a
     subtle tint when the user drags a file over it. Goes away on
     drop or dragleave. Pure CSS state driven by the JS class
     toggle below. */
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer.is-drop-target {
    background: rgba(56, 98, 170, .05);
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 2px var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
    transition: background .12s, box-shadow .12s;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer.is-drop-target #composer-input {
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer.is-drop-target::before {
    content: 'Drop file to attach';
    position: absolute; top: 50%; left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
    pointer-events: none; z-index: 5;
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer { position: relative; }   /* anchor for ::before */

  /* research toolbar above composer — verbatim port of the prototype's
     .rt-toggle look: small dot-pip + mono uppercase label + hairline
     | separators between toggles. Existing JS class names map onto it. */
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar {
    display: flex !important; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center;
    gap: 0 !important;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    padding: 6px 12px !important;
    background: var(--paper) !important;
    border: none !important;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    margin-bottom: 0 !important;
    border-radius: 0 !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat.privacy .composer-research-bar,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on .composer-research-bar {
    background: var(--privacy-tint) !important;
    border-bottom-color: var(--privacy);
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-state-label {
    font-size: 9px; color: var(--ink-4); letter-spacing: .14em;
    margin-right: 6px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-group {
    display: inline-flex !important; align-items: center; gap: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-group-label {
    font-size: 9px; color: var(--ink-4); letter-spacing: .14em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-right: 4px; margin-left: 4px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-divider {
    display: inline-block !important;
    width: 1px; height: 12px; background: var(--rule-soft);
    margin: 0 6px !important;
    font-size: 0;
    color: transparent;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar select.research-toggle-state,
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar #toggle-state {
    font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 11.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0; text-transform: none;
    color: var(--ink); background: transparent;
    border: none !important; cursor: pointer;
    border-bottom: 1px dotted var(--ink-3) !important;
    border-radius: 0 !important;
    padding: 2px 4px !important;
    margin: 0 6px;
    appearance: none; -webkit-appearance: none;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar select.research-toggle-state:focus,
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar #toggle-state:focus {
    outline: none; border-bottom-color: var(--accent-deep) !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-toggle {
    display: inline-flex !important; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 4px 8px !important;
    background: transparent !important; border: none !important;
    border-radius: 0 !important;
    cursor: pointer;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    transition: color .15s var(--motion-snap);
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-toggle:hover {
    color: var(--ink); background: transparent !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-toggle .research-toggle-label {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px; letter-spacing: .12em;
    text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 400;
  }
  /* Hide the native checkbox completely; the dot-pip is rendered via ::before */
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-toggle input[type="checkbox"] {
    appearance: none; -webkit-appearance: none;
    -moz-appearance: none;
    width: 7px; height: 7px; border-radius: 50%;
    border: 1px solid currentColor !important;
    margin: 0 !important;
    background: transparent !important;
    cursor: pointer;
    accent-color: currentColor;
    transition: background .15s;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-toggle input[type="checkbox"]:checked {
    background: currentColor !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-toggle:has(input:checked),
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-toggle:has(input:checked) .research-toggle-label {
    color: var(--accent-deep);
    font-weight: 500;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-research-bar .research-status {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px;
    letter-spacing: .08em; color: var(--ink-3);
  }

  /* composer input row */
  body.ws-chat form.chat-composer {
    display: grid !important;
    grid-template-columns: auto 1fr auto;
    align-items: end; gap: 12px;
    padding: 10px 18px 14px;
  }
  body.ws-chat #composer-paperclip {
    width: 38px; height: 42px;
    background: transparent; border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft); border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    color: var(--ink-3);
    transition: color .15s, border-color .15s, background .15s;
    align-self: flex-end;
  }
  body.ws-chat #composer-paperclip svg { width: 17px; height: 17px; }
  body.ws-chat #composer-paperclip:hover {
    color: var(--ink); border-color: var(--ink); background: rgba(255,255,255,.5);
  }
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer textarea,
  body.ws-chat #composer-input {
    width: 100%;
    font-family: var(--chat-font) !important;
    font-size: 15px !important; line-height: 1.55 !important;
    color: var(--ink);
    background: var(--paper-2);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft) !important; border-radius: 6px !important;
    padding: 12px 14px !important;
    resize: none;
    min-height: 64px !important; max-height: 220px;
    letter-spacing: -.005em;
    transition: border-color .15s, box-shadow .25s;
  }
  body.ws-chat #composer-input::placeholder {
    color: var(--ink-4);
    font-family: var(--chat-font);
    font-size: 15px; font-style: normal;
  }
  body.ws-chat #composer-input:focus {
    outline: none;
    border-color: var(--ink) !important;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--ink);
  }
  body.ws-chat.privacy #composer-input,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on #composer-input {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.4); border-color: var(--privacy) !important;
  }
  body.ws-chat.privacy #composer-input:focus,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on #composer-input:focus {
    border-color: var(--privacy) !important; box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px var(--privacy);
  }
  body.ws-chat #composer-send,
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer .ws-btn {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; gap: 8px;
    height: 42px; padding: 0 18px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10.5px; letter-spacing: .12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    background: var(--ink); color: var(--paper);
    border: 1px solid var(--ink); border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background .15s var(--motion-snap), border-color .15s, transform .12s;
    align-self: flex-end;
  }
  body.ws-chat #composer-send:hover,
  body.ws-chat .chat-composer .ws-btn:hover {
    background: var(--accent-deep); border-color: var(--accent-deep);
  }
  body.ws-chat #composer-send:active { transform: translateY(1px); }
  body.ws-chat.privacy #composer-send,
  body.ws-chat .chat-main.is-privacy-on #composer-send {
    background: var(--privacy); border-color: var(--privacy);
  }

  /* disclaimer */
  body.ws-chat .chat-discl {
    margin: 0; padding: 8px 28px 14px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 9.5px; color: var(--ink-3);
    letter-spacing: .08em; text-transform: uppercase;
    background: transparent;
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  /* attachments strip — sits above the composer input with a clear
     gap so the chips never look like they're crowding the textarea. */
  body.ws-chat .composer-attachments {
    padding: 4px 18px 8px;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 6px;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-attachments:empty {
    display: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-chip {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px;
    padding: 4px 8px 4px 9px;
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: .04em;
    color: var(--ink-2);
    background: rgba(56, 98, 170, .06);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
    border-radius: 3px;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-chip-icon {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    width: 12px; height: 12px;
    color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa);
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-chip-icon svg { width: 12px; height: 12px; }
  body.ws-chat .composer-chip-x {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    width: 16px; height: 16px; padding: 0;
    border: none; background: transparent;
    color: var(--ink-3); cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 14px; line-height: 1;
    opacity: .7;
  }
  body.ws-chat .composer-chip-x:hover { opacity: 1; color: var(--accent-deep, #3862aa); }
  /* In-bubble attachment chip — small inline pill with SVG paperclip. */
  body.ws-chat .msg-attach-icon {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
    width: 11px; height: 11px;
    color: var(--ink-3);
  }
  body.ws-chat .msg-attach-icon svg { width: 11px; height: 11px; }

  /* nav-toggle bar — keep it minimal to match the design */
  body.ws-chat #nav-toggle {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,.7);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-soft);
    backdrop-filter: blur(8px);
  }

  @media (max-width: 980px) {
    body.ws-chat .chat-shell { padding: 14px 16px; }
    body.ws-chat .chat-main { padding-left: 0; }
    body.ws-chat .chat-head { padding: 6px 18px 18px; }
    body.ws-chat .chat-messages { padding: 16px 18px; }
    body.ws-chat form.chat-composer { padding: 10px; gap: 8px; }
    body.ws-chat #composer-paperclip { display: none; }
  }
</style>
</head>
<body class="chat-page ws-chat">
<div id="grain"></div>

<header class="nav">
  <a href="/" class="brand">
    <svg class="brand-mark" viewBox="0 0 40 40"><circle cx="20" cy="20" r="18" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1"/><path d="M20 6 L20 34 M8 14 L32 14 M8 26 L32 26" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1" fill="none"/><circle cx="20" cy="14" r="2.5" fill="currentColor"/><circle cx="20" cy="26" r="2.5" fill="var(--accent)"/></svg>
    <span class="brand-text"><span>Legal</span><span class="brand-over">Overflow</span></span>
  </a>
  <nav class="nav-links">
    <a href="/#skills">Skills</a>
    <a href="/#articles">Resources</a>
    <a href="/agents/">Agents</a>
    <a href="/workspace/" class="is-active">Workspace</a>
    <a href="/tracker/">Tracker</a>
    <a href="/#services">Services</a>
    <a href="/about/">About</a>
  </nav>
  <div class="nav-right">
    <a href="/account/" class="nav-sub">Account</a>
  </div>
</header>

<!-- Collapse / expand the top nav so the chat has more vertical room.
     Sits flush along the bottom of the nav when expanded; floats at
     the top of the viewport when collapsed. -->
<button id="nav-toggle" class="nav-toggle" type="button" aria-label="Hide navigation" title="Hide navigation">
  <span class="nav-toggle-arrow">▲</span>
</button>

<main class="chat-shell">
  <aside class="chat-rail">
    <a href="/workspace/" class="chat-rail-back">← Workspace</a>
    <div class="side-head">
      <span class="side-kicker"><span class="pip"></span>WS / 04 · CHAT</span>
      <span class="side-title"><em>Conversation</em> log</span>
    </div>
    <button id="new-chat" class="chat-rail-new new-chat-btn">
      <span>New chat</span>
      <span class="plus">+</span>
    </button>
    <label class="side-search">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6"><circle cx="11" cy="11" r="7"></circle><path d="m20 20-4-4"></path></svg>
      <input type="text" id="chat-search" placeholder="Search conversations…" />
      <span class="kbd">⌘K</span>
    </label>
    <div id="rail-list" class="chat-rail-list side-list"></div>
  </aside>
  <!-- Draggable resize handle between sidebar and chat. -->
  <div id="rail-resize" class="rail-resize" role="separator" aria-label="Resize sidebar" aria-orientation="vertical" tabindex="0"></div>

  <section class="chat-main">
    <header class="chat-head">
      <span class="br-bl"></span><span class="br-br"></span>
      <div class="chat-kicker">
        <span class="k-tag">SESSION</span>
        <span class="k-coord" id="chat-coord">/WS · CHAT</span>
      </div>
      <div class="chat-head-row">
        <input type="text" id="chat-title" class="chat-title-input" placeholder="Untitled chat" />
        <div class="chat-head-right">
          <button type="button" id="chat-project-pill" class="chat-project-pill" aria-haspopup="true" title="Set project">
            <span id="chat-project-pill-label">…</span>
            <span class="chat-project-pill-caret">▾</span>
          </button>
          <div id="chat-project-popover" class="chat-project-popover" hidden></div>
          <!-- Save the entire conversation to the Vault as one item.
               Disabled when the chat has zero messages. -->
          <button type="button" id="save-convo-btn" class="chat-save-convo-btn" title="Save the entire conversation to your Vault">
            <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M19 21l-7-5-7 5V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10a2 2 0 0 1 2 2z"/>
            </svg>
            <span>Save conversation</span>
          </button>
          <label class="chat-privacy-toggle" id="chat-privacy-toggle" title="Privacy mode (FL Rule 4-1.6 / ABA Op. 512). Rewrites every message and attached document as an abstract hypothetical before sending — names, entities, dates, addresses, and amounts are stripped. The LLM never sees client-identifying content.">
            <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-privacy" />
            <span class="chat-privacy-toggle-label">Privacy</span>
          </label>
          <select id="model-select" class="chat-model-select" aria-label="Model"></select>
          <span id="model-vision-hint" class="chat-vision-hint" hidden title="This model reads images attached from your vault — embedded charts, signatures, diagrams, etc."></span>
          <!-- Deep-think toggle. When on AND the selected model
               supports extended reasoning (Claude 3.7+, o1/o3/o4,
               GPT-5, Gemini 2.5+, Grok 3+/4 reasoning), the chat
               request includes the provider's reasoning-effort
               knob set high. Hidden when the model doesn't
               support reasoning so the toggle never lies. -->
          <label class="chat-deep-think-toggle" id="chat-deep-think-toggle" hidden title="Deep think — gives the model a longer scratchpad before answering. Slower but better for complex legal reasoning. Only available on reasoning-capable models.">
            <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-deep-think" />
            <span class="chat-deep-think-toggle-label">Deep think</span>
          </label>
          <span id="key-source" class="chat-key-source" aria-live="polite"></span>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="chat-meta" id="chat-meta">
        <span><span class="ml">STARTED</span> &nbsp; <b id="chat-meta-started">—</b></span>
        <span><span class="ml">MESSAGES</span> &nbsp; <b id="chat-meta-msgs">0</b></span>
        <span><span class="ml">MODEL</span> &nbsp; <b id="chat-meta-model">—</b></span>
      </div>
      <!-- Anchor chip strip — pinned vault items that contribute
           guaranteed chunks + images to every turn. Hidden when
           there are no anchors. Suggestion pills (offering to
           anchor a doc that just contributed) render in the same
           strip with a dotted outline + "+" affordance. -->
      <div class="chat-anchors" id="chat-anchors" hidden></div>
    </header>
    <!-- Horizontal resize handle for the chat header. Drag vertically
         to expand or collapse. Persists in localStorage so the
         user's chosen height sticks across sessions. Same visual
         pattern as the sidebar's #rail-resize handle. -->
    <div id="chat-head-resize" class="chat-head-resize" role="separator" aria-label="Resize header" aria-orientation="horizontal" tabindex="0"></div>

    <div class="sec-div">
      <span class="sec-num">§ A</span>
      <span class="sec-rule"></span>
      <span class="sec-meta">STREAM · MOST RECENT BOTTOM</span>
    </div>

    <div class="chat-container">
      <div class="privacy-banner" id="privacy-banner">
        <span class="pb-pip"></span>
        <span><b>Privacy mode is on.</b>&nbsp; Every message and attached document is rewritten into an abstract legal hypothetical before it leaves the server — client names, entity names, addresses, dates, and dollar amounts are stripped. The LLM never sees client-identifying content. Vault snippets retrieved into this thread are abstracted the same way before they reach the model. (FL Rule 4-1.6 / ABA Op. 512.)</span>
      </div>
      <div id="messages" class="chat-messages">
        <div class="chat-empty">
          <div class="chat-empty-text">Ask something. The legal research desk is open.</div>
          <div class="suggested" id="suggested-prompts">
            <div class="suggested-head">— TRY ONE OF THESE TO START</div>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="What does Florida's prompt-payment statute (§ 218.74) say about late SaaS subscription invoices to a state agency?">
              <span class="sg-cat">— STATUTE</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt">Florida <em>prompt-payment</em> applicability to SaaS state-agency contracts</span>
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="Compare 'reasonable best efforts' vs. 'commercially reasonable efforts' under Delaware law and tell me which favors the obligor.">
              <span class="sg-cat">— DOCTRINE</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt">Reasonable <em>best efforts</em> vs. commercially reasonable (Delaware)</span>
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="Draft a mutual NDA confidentiality clause that survives termination by 3 years for trade secrets and indefinitely for intellectual property.">
              <span class="sg-cat">— DRAFTING</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt">Mutual <em>NDA</em> survival — 3 years / indefinite</span>
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="Summarize the key elements of a Florida tortious-interference claim and the leading defenses, with citations to controlling appellate authority.">
              <span class="sg-cat">— RESEARCH</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt">FL <em>tortious interference</em> — elements + defenses</span>
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="Draft a memo analyzing personal jurisdiction over a Florida defendant served via Florida's long-arm statute (§ 48.193) for a contract claim arising out of an out-of-state SaaS subscription.">
              <span class="sg-cat">— MEMO</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt">FL long-arm <em>personal jurisdiction</em> over a SaaS counterparty</span>
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="What's the standard for piercing the corporate veil under Delaware law, and how does it differ from Florida?">
              <span class="sg-cat">— DOCTRINE</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt"><em>Piercing the veil</em> — DE vs. FL standards</span>
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="I'm reviewing a SaaS MSA on the customer side. Walk me through the top 8 risk-allocation provisions I should pay closest attention to and what good looks like for each.">
              <span class="sg-cat">— REVIEW</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt">Customer-side <em>SaaS MSA</em> — top 8 risk provisions</span>
            </button>

            <button type="button" class="sg-card" data-prompt="Outline a deposition prep for a corporate representative deponent under FRCP 30(b)(6) on a breach-of-contract case. What objections should I be ready to make?">
              <span class="sg-cat">— LITIGATION</span>
              <span class="sg-prompt"><em>30(b)(6)</em> deposition prep + objection-spotting</span>
            </button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div id="composer-attachments" class="composer-attachments"></div>

    <!-- Research-mode toolbar — sits directly above the composer so
         the toggles are visually attached to the message the user is
         about to send. State persists per-chat in workspace_chats. -->
    <div id="research-bar" class="composer-research-bar">
      <span class="research-state-label" aria-hidden="true">State:</span>
      <select id="toggle-state" class="research-toggle-state" aria-label="State"
        data-tip="Sets which state any &ldquo;State&rdquo; toggle below applies to. Federal toggles ignore this."></select>

      <span class="research-divider" aria-hidden="true">|</span>
      <span class="research-group">
        <span class="research-group-label">Statutes:</span>
        <label class="research-toggle"
          data-tip="<b>State statutes.</b> Grounds the response in the selected state&rsquo;s codified statutes.">
          <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-state-statutes" />
          <span class="research-toggle-label">State</span>
        </label>
        <label class="research-toggle"
          data-tip="<b>Federal statutes.</b> Grounds the response in the U.S. Code and federal regulations.">
          <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-federal-statutes" />
          <span class="research-toggle-label">Federal</span>
        </label>
      </span>

      <span class="research-divider" aria-hidden="true">|</span>
      <span class="research-group">
        <span class="research-group-label">Case law:</span>
        <label class="research-toggle"
          data-tip="<b>State case law.</b> Pulls relevant decisions from the selected state&rsquo;s appellate and supreme courts.">
          <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-state-caselaw" />
          <span class="research-toggle-label">State</span>
        </label>
        <label class="research-toggle"
          data-tip="<b>Federal case law.</b> Pulls relevant decisions from the U.S. Supreme Court and the federal circuits. Citations are verified after the response.">
          <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-federal-caselaw" />
          <span class="research-toggle-label">Federal</span>
        </label>
      </span>

      <span class="research-divider" aria-hidden="true">|</span>
      <span class="research-group">
        <span class="research-group-label">Bills:</span>
        <label class="research-toggle"
          data-tip="<b>State bills.</b> Surfaces pending or recent legislation in the selected state, and flags cited statutes that may have pending amendments.">
          <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-state-bills" />
          <span class="research-toggle-label">State</span>
        </label>
        <label class="research-toggle"
          data-tip="<b>Federal bills.</b> Surfaces pending or recent legislation in the U.S. Congress, and flags cited federal statutes that may have pending amendments.">
          <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-federal-bills" />
          <span class="research-toggle-label">Federal</span>
        </label>
      </span>

      <span class="research-divider" aria-hidden="true">|</span>
      <label class="research-toggle research-toggle-vault"
        data-tip="<b>Your Vault.</b> Pulls relevant snippets from your saved docs, chat highlights, review findings, and notes into this chat as context. Per-chat — flip off to ignore your Vault for this conversation only.">
        <input type="checkbox" id="toggle-vault" />
        <span class="research-toggle-label">
          <svg class="research-toggle-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
            <path d="M3 7a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h4l2 2h8a2 2 0 0 1 2 2v9a2 2 0 0 1-2 2H5a2 2 0 0 1-2-2V7z"/>
          </svg>
          Vault
        </span>
      </label>

      <span class="research-status" id="research-status"></span>
    </div>

    <form id="composer" class="chat-composer">
      <button type="button" id="composer-paperclip" class="composer-paperclip" aria-label="Attach document" title="Attach document from library">
        <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M21.44 11.05l-9.19 9.19a6 6 0 1 1-8.49-8.49l9.19-9.19a4 4 0 0 1 5.66 5.66l-9.2 9.19a2 2 0 1 1-2.83-2.83l8.49-8.48"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
      <textarea id="composer-input" rows="2" placeholder="Ask a legal research question…"></textarea>
      <button type="submit" id="composer-send" class="ws-btn">Send</button>
    </form>
    </div><!-- /.chat-container -->
    <p class="chat-discl">Output is AI-generated and not legal advice. Verify every citation before relying on it.</p>

    <!-- Attach modal (hidden by default) -->
    <div id="attach-modal" class="attach-modal" hidden>
      <div class="attach-modal-inner">
        <header class="attach-modal-head">
          <h2 class="attach-modal-title">Attach document</h2>
          <button type="button" id="attach-close" class="attach-modal-close" aria-label="Close">×</button>
        </header>
        <div class="attach-modal-body">
          <div class="attach-upload-row">
            <button type="button" id="attach-upload-btn" class="ws-btn">+ Upload new</button>
            <input type="file" id="attach-upload-input" hidden multiple
              accept=".pdf,.docx,.txt,.md,application/pdf,application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document,text/plain,text/markdown" />
            <span class="attach-upload-hint">Goes into your library and auto-attaches</span>
          </div>
          <div id="attach-upload-progress" class="attach-upload-progress"></div>
          <input id="attach-search" class="attach-search" type="search" placeholder="Search your library…" />
          <div id="attach-list" class="attach-list">
            <div class="ws-empty">Loading…</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <footer class="attach-modal-foot">
          <a href="/workspace/library/" class="lib-back">Manage library →</a>
          <button type="button" id="attach-confirm" class="ws-btn" disabled>Attach selected</button>
        </footer>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Citation verification modal — opens when user clicks the
         small Citations summary pill below an assistant message,
         or any inline cite badge. Lists every detected citation
         with its verification status, source URL, and (when
         applicable) amendment notes from LegiScan. -->
    <div id="cite-modal" class="cite-modal" hidden>
      <div class="cite-modal-overlay"></div>
      <div class="cite-modal-inner">
        <header class="cite-modal-head">
          <h2 class="cite-modal-title">Citation verification</h2>
          <button type="button" class="cite-modal-close" data-cite-modal-close aria-label="Close">×</button>
        </header>
        <div class="cite-modal-body" id="cite-modal-body"></div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Save-conversation confirmation modal — opens when the user clicks
         the "Save conversation" button in the chat header. Explains what
         the Vault is and what gets saved before committing. -->
    <div id="save-convo-modal" class="cite-modal" hidden>
      <div class="cite-modal-overlay" data-save-modal-close></div>
      <div class="cite-modal-inner">
        <header class="cite-modal-head">
          <h2 class="cite-modal-title">Save this conversation to your Vault?</h2>
          <button type="button" class="cite-modal-close" data-save-modal-close aria-label="Close">×</button>
        </header>
        <div class="cite-modal-body">
          <p>The <strong>Vault</strong> is your private long-term knowledge base. Anything you save there is searchable and can be pulled into future chats automatically (toggle the <em>🗂 Vault</em> switch above the composer in any thread).</p>
          <p><strong>What this save will do:</strong></p>
          <ul style="font-size: 13.5px; line-height: 1.55; padding-left: 20px;">
            <li>Copies the entire conversation — your questions and the assistant's answers — into a single Vault item.</li>
            <li>Indexes it for semantic search so you can find it later by topic, not just by chat title.</li>
            <li>Makes it eligible for retrieval into other chats. (Per-chat — you can flip Vault retrieval off in any thread.)</li>
            <li>Stays in <strong>your</strong> Vault only. Nothing is shared with other users.</li>
